1 Serv ices as required by the Office of Management and Enterprise
2 Services.
3 B. The form shall include, but shall not be limited to, the
4 following:
5 1. The legal name of the entity proposing to manage the federal
6 funds pursuant to contract, including any trade name or similar name
7 which is not the formal legal name of the entity that will enter
8 into the contract;
9 2. The jurisdiction in which the prospective vendor entity was
10 originally incorporated or otherwise created pursuant to the laws of
11 the applicable jurisdiction;
12 3. The legal names of the principal officers of the prospective
13 vendor entity which proposes to manage the federal funds, which may
14 include, but shall not be limited to the chief executive officer,
15 the chief financial officer, the chief information or technology
16 officer and the chief operating officer;
17 4. A listing of the prior experience of the prospective vendor
18 entity or its officers or employees with regard to the management of
19 federal funds on behalf of any state or local government entity;
20 5. The most recently completed financial audit of the books and
21 records of the prospective vendor entity prior to the date as of
22 which the form prescribed pursuant to the provisions of this section
23 is submitted to the Office of Management and Enterprise Services, in
24 cases involving a vendor with no prior experience in the management
